Citation.sAbstract: The vapor liquid equilibria in the seven ternary systems water + toluene + aniline, water + octane + aniline, water + toluene + cyclohexylamine,  water + octane + cyclohexylamine, toluene + aniline + cyclohexylamine, octane + aniline + cyclohexylamine, andwater + cyclohexylamine + aniline  were determined at 333.15 and 363.15Kat reduced pressure. The experimental results were compared with the predictions of the activity coefficient  models UNIQUAC and NRTL and the equation of state proposed by Elliott, Suresh, and Donohue (ESD EOS).
Citation.sTitle: Vapor liquid equilibria in ternary systems of associating components (water, aniline, cyclohexylamine) and hydrocarbons (octane or toluene)
